100 *
101 * Resource Tag tables
102 *
103 * These are the predefined tags that refer to elements of a resource
104 * descriptor. Each name and offset is defined in the ACPI specification.
105 *
106 * Each table entry contains the bit offset of the field and the associated
107 * name.
108 *
109 ******************************************************************************/

367/*

369 *
370 * A NULL in this table means one of three things:

373 * 3) The descriptor has subtypes and a separate table will be used.
374 */

376{

385 NULL, /* 0x06, ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_START_DEPENDENT */

387 AcpiDmIoTags, /* 0x08, ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_IO_PORT */
388 AcpiDmFixedIoTags, /* 0x09, ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_FIXED_IO_PORT */
389 AcpiDmFixedDmaTags, /* 0x0A, ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_FIXED_DMA */

391 NULL, /* 0x0C, Reserved */
392 NULL, /* 0x0D, Reserved */
393 NULL, /* 0x0E, ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_SMALL_VENDOR */

437/*
438 * Globals used to generate unique resource descriptor names. We use names that
439 * start with underscore and a prefix letter that is not used by other ACPI
440 * reserved names. To this, we append hex 0x00 through 0xFF. These 5 prefixes
441 * allow for 5*256 = 1280 unique names, probably sufficient for any single ASL
442 * file. If this becomes too small, we can use alpha+numerals for a total
443 * of 5*36*36 = 6480.
444 */
445#define ACPI_NUM_RES_PREFIX 5
446
447static UINT32 AcpiGbl_NextResourceId = 0;
448static UINT8 AcpiGbl_NextPrefix = 0;
449static char AcpiGbl_Prefix[ACPI_NUM_RES_PREFIX] =
450 {'Y','Z','J','K','X'};

453/*******************************************************************************
454 *
455 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmCheckResourceReference
456 *
457 * PARAMETERS: Op - Parse Op for the AML opcode
458 * WalkState - Current walk state (with valid scope)
459 *
460 * RETURN: None
461 *
462 * DESCRIPTION: Convert a reference to a resource descriptor to a symbolic
463 * reference if possible
464 *
465 * NOTE: Bit index is used to transparently handle both resource bit
466 * fields and byte fields.
467 *
468 ******************************************************************************/
469
470void
471AcpiDmCheckResourceReference (
472 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *Op,
473 ACPI_WALK_STATE *WalkState)
474{
475 ACPI_STATUS Status;
476 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *BufferNameOp;
477 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *IndexOp;
478 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *BufferNode;
479 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *ResourceNode;
480 const ACPI_OPCODE_INFO *OpInfo;
481 UINT32 BitIndex;
482
483
484 /* We are only interested in the CreateXxxxField opcodes */
485
486 OpInfo = AcpiPsGetOpcodeInfo (Op->Common.AmlOpcode);
487 if (OpInfo->Type != AML_TYPE_CREATE_FIELD)
488 {
489 return;
490 }
491
492 /* Get the buffer term operand */
493
494 BufferNameOp = AcpiPsGetDepthNext (NULL, Op);
495
496 /* Must be a named buffer, not an arg or local or method call */
497
498 if (BufferNameOp->Common.AmlOpcode != AML_INT_NAMEPATH_OP)
499 {
500 return;
501 }
502
503 /* Get the Index term, must be an integer constant to convert */
504
505 IndexOp = BufferNameOp->Common.Next;
506
507 /* Major cheat: The Node field is also used for the Tag ptr. Clear it now */
508
509 IndexOp->Common.Node = NULL;
510
511 OpInfo = AcpiPsGetOpcodeInfo (IndexOp->Common.AmlOpcode);
512 if (OpInfo->ObjectType != ACPI_TYPE_INTEGER)
513 {
514 return;
515 }
516
517 /* Get the bit offset of the descriptor within the buffer */
518
519 if ((Op->Common.AmlOpcode == AML_CREATE_BIT_FIELD_OP) ||
520 (Op->Common.AmlOpcode == AML_CREATE_FIELD_OP))
521 {
522 /* Index operand is a bit offset */
523
524 BitIndex = (UINT32) IndexOp->Common.Value.Integer;
525 }
526 else
527 {
528 /* Index operand is a byte offset, convert to bits */
529
530 BitIndex = (UINT32) ACPI_MUL_8 (IndexOp->Common.Value.Integer);
531 }
532
533 /* Lookup the buffer in the namespace */
534
535 Status = AcpiNsLookup (WalkState->ScopeInfo,
536 BufferNameOp->Common.Value.String, ACPI_TYPE_BUFFER,
537 ACPI_IMODE_EXECUTE, ACPI_NS_SEARCH_PARENT, WalkState,
538 &BufferNode);
539 if (ACPI_FAILURE (Status))
540 {
541 return;
542 }
543
544 /* Validate object type, we must have a buffer */
545
546 if (BufferNode->Type != ACPI_TYPE_BUFFER)
547 {
548 return;
549 }
550
551 /* Find the resource descriptor node corresponding to the index */
552
553 ResourceNode = AcpiDmGetResourceNode (BufferNode, BitIndex);
554 if (!ResourceNode)
555 {
556 return;
557 }
558
559 /* Translate the Index to a resource tag pathname */
560
561 AcpiGetTagPathname (IndexOp, BufferNode, ResourceNode, BitIndex);
562}
563
564
565/*******************************************************************************
566 *
567 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmGetResourceNode
568 *
569 * PARAMETERS: BufferNode - Node for the parent buffer
570 * BitIndex - Index into the resource descriptor
571 *
572 * RETURN: Namespace node for the resource descriptor. NULL if not found
573 *
574 * DESCRIPTION: Find a resource descriptor that corresponds to the bit index
575 *
576 ******************************************************************************/
577
578static ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *
579AcpiDmGetResourceNode (
580 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *BufferNode,
581 UINT32 BitIndex)
582{
583 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *Node;
584 UINT32 ByteIndex = ACPI_DIV_8 (BitIndex);
585
586
587 /*
588 * Child list contains an entry for each resource descriptor. Find
589 * the descriptor that corresponds to the Index.
590 *
591 * If there are no children, this is not a resource template
592 */
593 Node = BufferNode->Child;
594 while (Node)
595 {
596 /*
597 * Check if the Index falls within this resource.
598 *
599 * Value contains the resource offset, Object contains the resource
600 * length (both in bytes)
601 */
602 if ((ByteIndex >= Node->Value) &&
603 (ByteIndex < (Node->Value + Node->Length)))
604 {
605 return (Node);
606 }
607
608 Node = Node->Peer;
609 }
610
611 return (NULL);
612}
613
614
615/*******************************************************************************
616 *
617 * FUNCTION: AcpiGetTagPathname
618 *
619 * PARAMETERS: BufferNode - Node for the parent buffer
620 * ResourceNode - Node for a resource descriptor
621 * BitIndex - Index into the resource descriptor
622 *
623 * RETURN: Full pathname for a resource tag. NULL if no match.
624 * Path is returned in AML (packed) format.
625 *
626 * DESCRIPTION: Convert a BitIndex into a symbolic resource tag (full pathname)
627 *
628 ******************************************************************************/
629
630static char *
631AcpiGetTagPathname (
632 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *IndexOp,
633 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *BufferNode,
634 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *ResourceNode,
635 UINT32 BitIndex)
636{
637 ACPI_STATUS Status;
638 UINT32 ResourceBitIndex;
639 UINT8 ResourceTableIndex;
640 ACPI_SIZE RequiredSize;
641 char *Pathname;
642 char *PathnameEnd;
643 AML_RESOURCE *Aml;
644 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *Op;
645 char *InternalPath;
646 char *Tag;
647
648
649 /* Get the Op that contains the actual buffer data */
650
651 Op = BufferNode->Op->Common.Value.Arg;
652 Op = Op->Common.Next;
653 if (!Op)
654 {
655 return (NULL);
656 }
657
658 /* Get the individual resource descriptor and validate it */
659
660 Aml = ACPI_CAST_PTR (
661 AML_RESOURCE, &Op->Named.Data[ResourceNode->Value]);
662
663 Status = AcpiUtValidateResource (NULL, Aml, &ResourceTableIndex);
664 if (ACPI_FAILURE (Status))
665 {
666 return (NULL);
667 }
668
669 /* Get offset into this descriptor (from offset into entire buffer) */
670
671 ResourceBitIndex = BitIndex - ACPI_MUL_8 (ResourceNode->Value);
672
673 /* Get the tag associated with this resource descriptor and offset */
674
675 Tag = AcpiDmGetResourceTag (ResourceBitIndex, Aml, ResourceTableIndex);
676 if (!Tag)
677 {
678 return (NULL);
679 }
680
681 /*
682 * Now that we know that we have a reference that can be converted to a
683 * symbol, change the name of the resource to a unique name.
684 */
685 AcpiDmUpdateResourceName (ResourceNode);
686
687 /* Get the full pathname to the parent buffer */
688
689 RequiredSize = AcpiNsBuildNormalizedPath (BufferNode, NULL, 0, FALSE);
690 if (!RequiredSize)
691 {
692 return (NULL);
693 }
694
695 Pathname = ACPI_ALLOCATE_ZEROED (RequiredSize + ACPI_PATH_SEGMENT_LENGTH);
696 if (!Pathname)
697 {
698 return (NULL);
699 }
700
701 (void) AcpiNsBuildNormalizedPath (BufferNode, Pathname,
702 RequiredSize, FALSE);
703
704 /*
705 * Create the full path to the resource and tag by:
706 * 1) Remove the buffer nameseg from the end of the pathname
707 * 2) Append the resource descriptor nameseg
708 * 3) Append a dot
709 * 4) Append the field tag nameseg
710 *
711 * Always using the full path is a bit brute force, the path can be
712 * often be optimized with carats (if the original buffer namepath is a
713 * single nameseg). This doesn't really matter, because these paths do not
714 * end up in the final compiled AML, it's just an appearance issue for the
715 * disassembled code.
716 */
717 PathnameEnd = Pathname + (RequiredSize - ACPI_NAMESEG_SIZE - 1);
718 ACPI_COPY_NAMESEG (PathnameEnd, ResourceNode->Name.Ascii);
719
720 PathnameEnd += ACPI_NAMESEG_SIZE;
721 *PathnameEnd = '.';
722
723 PathnameEnd++;
724 ACPI_COPY_NAMESEG (PathnameEnd, Tag);
725
726 /* Internalize the namepath to AML format */
727
728 AcpiNsInternalizeName (Pathname, &InternalPath);
729 ACPI_FREE (Pathname);
730
731 /* Update the Op with the symbol */
732
733 AcpiPsInitOp (IndexOp, AML_INT_NAMEPATH_OP);
734 IndexOp->Common.Value.String = InternalPath;
735
736 /*
737 * We will need the tag later. Cheat by putting it in the Node field.
738 * Note, Tag is a const that is part of a lookup table.
739 */
740 IndexOp->Common.Node = ACPI_CAST_PTR (ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE, Tag);
741 return (InternalPath);
742}
743
744
745/*******************************************************************************
746 *
747 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmUpdateResourceName
748 *
749 * PARAMETERS: ResourceNode - Node for a resource descriptor
750 *
751 * RETURN: Stores new name in the ResourceNode
752 *
753 * DESCRIPTION: Create a new, unique name for a resource descriptor. Used by
754 * both the disassembly of the descriptor itself and any symbolic
755 * references to the descriptor. Ignored if a unique name has
756 * already been assigned to the resource.
757 *
758 * NOTE: Single threaded, suitable for applications only!
759 *
760 ******************************************************************************/
761
762static void
763AcpiDmUpdateResourceName (
764 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *ResourceNode)
765{
766 char Name[ACPI_NAMESEG_SIZE];
767
768
769 /* Ignore if a unique name has already been assigned */
770
771 if (ResourceNode->Name.Integer != ACPI_DEFAULT_RESNAME)
772 {
773 return;
774 }
775
776 /* Generate a new ACPI name for the descriptor */
777
778 Name[0] = '_';
779 Name[1] = AcpiGbl_Prefix[AcpiGbl_NextPrefix];
780 Name[2] = AcpiUtHexToAsciiChar ((UINT64) AcpiGbl_NextResourceId, 4);
781 Name[3] = AcpiUtHexToAsciiChar ((UINT64) AcpiGbl_NextResourceId, 0);
782
783 /* Update globals for next name */
784
785 AcpiGbl_NextResourceId++;
786 if (AcpiGbl_NextResourceId >= 256)
787 {
788 AcpiGbl_NextResourceId = 0;
789 AcpiGbl_NextPrefix++;
790
791 if (AcpiGbl_NextPrefix > ACPI_NUM_RES_PREFIX)
792 {
793 AcpiGbl_NextPrefix = 0;
794 }
795 }
796
797 /* Change the resource descriptor name */
798
799 ResourceNode->Name.Integer = *ACPI_CAST_PTR (UINT32, &Name[0]);
800}

803/*******************************************************************************
804 *
805 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmGetResourceTag
806 *
807 * PARAMETERS: BitIndex - Index into the resource descriptor
808 * Resource - Pointer to the raw resource data
809 * ResourceIndex - Index corresponding to the resource type
810 *
811 * RETURN: Pointer to the resource tag (ACPI_NAME). NULL if no match.
812 *
813 * DESCRIPTION: Convert a BitIndex into a symbolic resource tag.
814 *
815 * Note: ResourceIndex should be previously validated and guaranteed to ve
816 * valid.
817 *
818 ******************************************************************************/
819
820static char *
821AcpiDmGetResourceTag (
822 UINT32 BitIndex,
823 AML_RESOURCE *Resource,
824 UINT8 ResourceIndex)
825{
826 const ACPI_RESOURCE_TAG *TagList;
827 char *Tag = NULL;
828
829
830 /* Get the tag list for this resource descriptor type */
831
832 TagList = AcpiGbl_ResourceTags[ResourceIndex];
833
834 /*
835 * Handle descriptors that have multiple subtypes
836 */
837 switch (Resource->DescriptorType)
838 {
839 case ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_ADDRESS16:
840 case ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_ADDRESS32:
841 case ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_ADDRESS64:
842 case ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_EXTENDED_ADDRESS64:
843 /*
844 * Subtype differentiation is the flags.
845 * Kindof brute force, but just blindly search for an index match
846 */
847 if (Resource->Address.ResourceType == ACPI_ADDRESS_TYPE_MEMORY_RANGE)
848 {
849 Tag = AcpiDmSearchTagList (BitIndex, AcpiDmMemoryFlagTags);
850 }
851 else if (Resource->Address.ResourceType == ACPI_ADDRESS_TYPE_IO_RANGE)
852 {
853 Tag = AcpiDmSearchTagList (BitIndex, AcpiDmIoFlagTags);
854 }
855
856 /* If we found a match, all done. Else, drop to normal search below */
857
858 if (Tag)
859 {
860 return (Tag);
861 }
862 break;
863
864 case ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_GPIO:
865
866 /* GPIO connection has 2 subtypes: Interrupt and I/O */
867
868 if (Resource->Gpio.ConnectionType > AML_RESOURCE_MAX_GPIOTYPE)
869 {
870 return (NULL);
871 }
872
873 TagList = AcpiGbl_GpioResourceTags[Resource->Gpio.ConnectionType];
874 break;
875
876 case ACPI_RESOURCE_NAME_SERIAL_BUS:
877
878 /* SerialBus has 3 subtypes: I2C, SPI, and UART */
879
880 if ((Resource->CommonSerialBus.Type == 0) ||
881 (Resource->CommonSerialBus.Type > AML_RESOURCE_MAX_SERIALBUSTYPE))
882 {
883 return (NULL);
884 }
885
886 TagList = AcpiGbl_SerialResourceTags[Resource->CommonSerialBus.Type];
887 break;
888
889 default:
890
891 break;
892 }
893
894 /* Search for a match against the BitIndex */
895
896 if (TagList)
897 {
898 Tag = AcpiDmSearchTagList (BitIndex, TagList);
899 }
900
901 return (Tag);
902}
903
904
905/*******************************************************************************
906 *
907 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmSearchTagList
908 *
909 * PARAMETERS: BitIndex - Index into the resource descriptor
910 * TagList - List to search
911 *
912 * RETURN: Pointer to a tag (ACPI_NAME). NULL if no match found.
913 *
914 * DESCRIPTION: Search a tag list for a match to the input BitIndex. Matches
915 * a fixed offset to a symbolic resource tag name.
916 *
917 ******************************************************************************/
918
919static char *
920AcpiDmSearchTagList (
921 UINT32 BitIndex,
922 const ACPI_RESOURCE_TAG *TagList)
923{
924
925 /*
926 * Walk the null-terminated tag list to find a matching bit offset.
927 * We are looking for an exact match.
928 */
929 for ( ; TagList->Tag; TagList++)
930 {
931 if (BitIndex == TagList->BitIndex)
932 {
933 return (TagList->Tag);
934 }
935 }
936
937 /* A matching offset was not found */
938
939 return (NULL);
940}

943/*******************************************************************************
944 *
945 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmFindResources
946 *
947 * PARAMETERS: Root - Root of the parse tree
948 *
949 * RETURN: None
950 *
951 * DESCRIPTION: Add all ResourceTemplate declarations to the namespace. Each
952 * resource descriptor in each template is given a node -- used
953 * for later conversion of resource references to symbolic refs.
954 *
955 ******************************************************************************/
956
957void
958AcpiDmFindResources (
959 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *Root)
960{
961 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *Op = Root;
962 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *Parent;
963
964
965 /* Walk the entire parse tree */
966
967 while (Op)
968 {
969 /* We are interested in Buffer() declarations */
970
971 if (Op->Common.AmlOpcode == AML_BUFFER_OP)
972 {
973 /* And only declarations of the form Name (XXXX, Buffer()... ) */
974
975 Parent = Op->Common.Parent;
976 if (Parent->Common.AmlOpcode == AML_NAME_OP)
977 {
978 /*
979 * If the buffer is a resource template, add the individual
980 * resource descriptors to the namespace, as children of the
981 * buffer node.
982 */
983 if (ACPI_SUCCESS (AcpiDmIsResourceTemplate (NULL, Op)))
984 {
985 Op->Common.DisasmOpcode = ACPI_DASM_RESOURCE;
986 AcpiDmAddResourcesToNamespace (Parent->Common.Node, Op);
987 }
988 }
989 }
990
991 Op = AcpiPsGetDepthNext (Root, Op);
992 }
993}
994
995
996/*******************************************************************************
997 *
998 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmAddResourcesToNamespace
999 *
1000 * PARAMETERS: BufferNode - Node for the parent buffer
1001 * Op - Parse op for the buffer
1002 *
1003 * RETURN: None
1004 *
1005 * DESCRIPTION: Add an entire resource template to the namespace. Each
1006 * resource descriptor is added as a namespace node.
1007 *
1008 ******************************************************************************/
1009
1010static void
1011AcpiDmAddResourcesToNamespace (
1012 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *BufferNode,
1013 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *Op)
1014{
1015 ACPI_PARSE_OBJECT *NextOp;
1016
1017
1018 /* Get to the ByteData list */
1019
1020 NextOp = Op->Common.Value.Arg;
1021 NextOp = NextOp->Common.Next;
1022 if (!NextOp)
1023 {
1024 return;
1025 }
1026
1027 /* Set Node and Op to point to each other */
1028
1029 BufferNode->Op = Op;
1030 Op->Common.Node = BufferNode;
1031
1032 /*
1033 * Insert each resource into the namespace
1034 * NextOp contains the Aml pointer and the Aml length
1035 */
1036 AcpiUtWalkAmlResources (NULL, (UINT8 *) NextOp->Named.Data,
1037 (ACPI_SIZE) NextOp->Common.Value.Integer,
1038 AcpiDmAddResourceToNamespace, (void **) BufferNode);
1039}
1040
1041
1042/*******************************************************************************
1043 *
1044 * FUNCTION: AcpiDmAddResourceToNamespace
1045 *
1046 * PARAMETERS: ACPI_WALK_AML_CALLBACK
1047 * BufferNode - Node for the parent buffer
1048 *
1049 * RETURN: Status
1050 *
1051 * DESCRIPTION: Add one resource descriptor to the namespace as a child of the
1052 * parent buffer. The same name is used for each descriptor. This
1053 * is changed later to a unique name if the resource is actually
1054 * referenced by an AML operator.
1055 *
1056 ******************************************************************************/
1057
1058static ACPI_STATUS
1059AcpiDmAddResourceToNamespace (
1060 UINT8 *Aml,
1061 UINT32 Length,
1062 UINT32 Offset,
1063 UINT8 ResourceIndex,
1064 void **Context)
1065{
1066 ACPI_STATUS Status;
1067 ACPI_GENERIC_STATE ScopeInfo;
1068 ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE *Node;
1069
1070
1071 /* TBD: Don't need to add descriptors that have no tags defined? */
1072
1073 /* Add the resource to the namespace, as child of the buffer */
1074
1075 ScopeInfo.Scope.Node = ACPI_CAST_PTR (ACPI_NAMESPACE_NODE, Context);
1076 Status = AcpiNsLookup (&ScopeInfo, "_TMP", ACPI_TYPE_LOCAL_RESOURCE,
1077 ACPI_IMODE_LOAD_PASS2,
1078 ACPI_NS_NO_UPSEARCH | ACPI_NS_DONT_OPEN_SCOPE | ACPI_NS_PREFIX_IS_SCOPE,
1079 NULL, &Node);
1080 if (ACPI_FAILURE (Status))
1081 {
1082 return (AE_OK);
1083 }
1084
1085 /* Set the name to the default, changed later if resource is referenced */
1086
1087 Node->Name.Integer = ACPI_DEFAULT_RESNAME;
1088
1089 /* Save the offset of the descriptor (within the original buffer) */
1090
1091 Node->Value = Offset;
1092 Node->Length = Length;
1093 return (AE_OK);
1094}
